<p>From Gerald Lynton Kaufman&#8217;s <a href="https://archive.org/details/bookofmodernpuzz0000gera_f8z2/page/88/mode/2up"><em>The Book of Modern Puzzles</em></a> (1954):</p>
<ol>
<li>All DROONS are the same size and shape.</li>
<li>All green SLACKENS are the same size and shape.</li>
<li>Twenty DROONS just fill up a MULDRUFF.</li>
<li>All WALLAXES contain green SLACKENS.</li>
<li>A green SLACKEN is 10% bigger than a DROON.</li>
<li>A WALLAX is smaller than a MULDRUFF.</li>
</ol>
<p>&#8220;If all MULDRUFFS and all WALLAXES are predominantly RED throughout, what is the largest possible number of green SLACKENS in a WALLAX?&#8221;</p>

<div class='easySpoilerWrapper' style=''>
